      "_id": "MPParagraphElement:8C9E7E71-EF67-4957-A6B4-79B268EE3D84",
      "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:8C9E7E71-EF67-4957-A6B4-79B268EE3D84\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">The survey is analyzed following a process developed by Kitchenham [<span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"MPCitation:0714F39E-6F57-4193-96D0-0E1EA49C1CD2\">40</span>, <span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"MPCitation:C8C99CE6-B337-44C2-8FCC-556E2D2C68A6\">41</span>] called systematic literature review (SLR). This article divides the SLR processes into three different parts: the planning phase, the conducting phase, and the reporting phase. In the subsequent sections, the steps are discussed in detail.</p>",
      "createdAt": 1694167156,
      "updatedAt": 1694167156,
      "objectType": "MPParagraphElement",
      "containerID": "MPProject:c4855a02-050a-452c-af9d-3a2e4501a96e",
