      "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:6760DDB9-3173-4D27-BF27-4C5486D3A665\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">Aside from this, there are other types of accuracy, such as predictive accuracy and average accuracy. Predictive accuracy should be estimated based on the difference between observed and predicted values [<span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"null\">354</span>, <span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"null\">355</span>]. Average accuracy is the average of every accuracy per class (amount of accuracy for each class anticipated/number of classes) [<span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"null\">356</span>].</p>",
