      "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:63BAB670-C157-4CBB-B9C7-36ADEB8ADC43\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">RAE is a way of estimating the performance of a proactive model. RAE is a metric contrasting genuine figure error with the estimated error of a shortsighted (naive) model. A sensible model (which produces results that are superior to a trivial model) will bring about a proportion short of one [<span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"null\">391</span>, <span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"null\">392</span>].</p>",
      "createdAt": 1694167156,
      "updatedAt": 1694167156,
