    },
    {
      "_id": "MPParagraphElement:F60214D7-7321-4397-997E-4945D940AA93",
      "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:F60214D7-7321-4397-997E-4945D940AA93\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">Most nodules are harmless, indicating a more severe health issue. Among other tissues, parenchymal tissues are distinct and difficult to segment. On the other hand, solitary and large solid nodules are easy for segmentation. But the problem occurs when these types of nodules are targeted.</p>",
      "createdAt": 1694167156,
      "updatedAt": 1694167156,
