      ],
      "title": "11.5. Efficient CADe System",
      "priority": 110,
      "createdAt": 1694167156,
      "updatedAt": 1694167156,
      "elementIDs": ["MPParagraphElement:7F55A2BB-42CA-422F-948A-71A76FE58FAE"],
      "objectType": "MPSection",
      "containerID": "MPProject:c4855a02-050a-452c-af9d-3a2e4501a96e",
      "manuscriptID": "MPManuscript:df7d82ce-e66f-402a-9015-637248ba4cbc"
    },
    {
      "_id": "MPParagraphElement:1DD8DC9E-50FC-4410-905F-FBD6785BB76F",
      "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:1DD8DC9E-50FC-4410-905F-FBD6785BB76F\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">Volumetric measurements are essential because various sizes in different situations make the system more accurate. When calculating the growth rate in the volumetric unit, the global movement of patients caused by their actions and the local activity of the entire lung tissue caused by respiration and heartbeat should be considered. It is impossible to distinguish between changes caused by the direct application of global and local registration to the segmented nodule and changes in the shape of the nodule caused by breathing and heartbeat.</p>",
      "createdAt": 1694167156,
      "updatedAt": 1694167156,
      "objectType": "MPParagraphElement",
      "containerID": "MPProject:c4855a02-050a-452c-af9d-3a2e4501a96e",
